Rockwell Diamonds, Oasis, Old Mutual May Move: South Africa Equity Preview

-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 
2011-05-11T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/rockwell-diamonds-oasis-afgri-south-africa-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index of stocks fell 34.21,
or 0.1 percent, to 32,051.35 in Johannesburg.  Oasis Crescent Property Fund (OAS)  : The exchange-traded
property fund said net income retreated to 46 million rand ($7
million) from 56 million rand a year earlier, according to a
regulatory filing released after the market closed yesterday.
The stock was unchanged at 12.90 rand.  Old Mutual Plc (OML)  : The third-biggest insurer in the
U.K. by market value releases first-quarter results and holds an
annual general meeting. The shares added 8 cents, or 0.5
percent, to 15.10 rand.  Rockwell Diamonds Inc. (RDI)  : The company, which mines
for diamonds in the Democratic Republic of Congo, appointed
James Campbell as president and chief executive officer. The
shares were unchanged at 30 cents.  The following shares begin trading without the right to
their latest dividend:  Afgri Ltd. (AFR)  ,  Brait SA (BAT)  ,  Consolidated
Infrastructure Group Ltd. (CIL)  ,  Octodec Investments Ltd. (OCT) 
,  Premium Properties Ltd. (PMM)  ,  Simmer & Jack Mines
Ltd. (SIM)   and  UCS Group Ltd. (UCS)  .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Brand in Cape Town Nef at 
